With the grep command we can find a keyword within a file. Using -n will list the line number of the kleyword is located.

//using the command below, we will find all lines containing the word linux in the two files info and infotwo.txt
grep -n "linux" info.txt infotwo.txt


//using grep and find together can help us locate files containing a specific keyword
find / -name *.php -exec grep -n function {} +
